text.tspan: Movie order is optimized with a meta heuristic approach, in detail simulated annealing. The cost is defined as
the divergence of movies, of the same director, from their centroid. This will optimally result in a minimum
number of crossings between movies directed by the same director. The original graph is rendered with D3,
while further adjustments are performed using Inkscape.
Images of movies are accessed from IMDB. Movie Reel
background from svgsilh.com. The movie data is provided
by the 29th International Symposium on Graph
Graph Drawing Contest 2021 · Ammer David · Korpitsch Thorsten · Pointner Simon
